import numpy as np
import cv2 as cv
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
img= cv.imread(r'Images/spider.png',cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
assert img is not None
gamma = [0.2,0.8,1.2,2]
for i in gamma:
    t= np.array([(p/255)**i*255 for p in range(0,256)]).astype(np.uint8)
    g=cv.LUT(img,t)
    fig,ax=plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(t)
    ax.title.set_text(f"gamma = %f" % i)
    cv.namedWindow('Image',cv.WINDOW_AUTOSIZE)
    cv.imshow('image',img)
    cv.waitKey(0)
    cv.imshow('gamma corrected image',g)
    cv.waitKey(0)
    cv.destroyAllWindows()

    plt.figure()
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title("original image")
    plt.show()
    plt.figure(0)
    plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(g, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(f"gamma = %f corrected image" % i)
    plt.show()

import numpy as np
import cv2 as cv
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
img= cv.imread(r'Images/spider.png',cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
assert img is not None
t1=np.linspace(0,100,50)
t2=np.linspace(100,255,150)
t3=np.linspace(255,255,56)
t=np.concatenate((t1,t2,t3),axis=0).astype(np.uint8)
fig,ax=plt.subplots()
ax.plot(t)
ax.title.set_text("Intensity transformation")
ax.set_aspect('equal')
assert len(t)==256
g=cv.LUT(img,t)
cv.namedWindow('Image',cv.WINDOW_AUTOSIZE)
cv.imshow('image',img)
cv.waitKey(0)
cv.imshow('image',g)
cv.waitKey(0)
cv.destroyAllWindows()

plt.figure()
plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title("original image")
plt.show()
plt.figure()
plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(g, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title("Intensity transformed image")
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import cv2 as cv
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
img= cv.imread(r'Images/shells.tif',cv.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE)
assert img is not None
hist_img=cv.calcHist([img],[0],None,[256],[0,256])
g=cv.equalizeHist(img)
hist_g=cv.calcHist([g],[0],None,[256],[0,256])
fig,ax = plt.subplots(2,1,figsize=(8,8))
ax[0].plot(hist_img)
ax[0].title.set_text("Histogram of Original image")
ax[1].plot(hist_g)
ax[1].title.set_text("Histogram of equalized image")

cv.namedWindow('Image',cv.WINDOW_AUTOSIZE)
cv.imshow('image',img)
cv.waitKey(0)
cv.imshow('image',g)
cv.waitKey(0)
cv.destroyAllWindows()

plt.figure()
plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title("Original image")
plt.show()
plt.figure()
plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(g, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title("Histogram equalized image")
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import cv2 as cv
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
img= cv.imread(r'Images/zion_pass.jpg',cv.IMREAD_COLOR)
assert img is not None
hsv = cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2HSV)
h,s,v = cv.split(hsv)
hnew = np.mod(h + 50, 180).astype(np.uint8)
snew=np.mod(s + 10, 180).astype(np.uint8)
vnew=np.mod(v - 50, 180).astype(np.uint8)
hsv_new = cv.merge([hnew,snew,vnew])
img_new = cv.cvtColor(hsv_new, cv.COLOR_HSV2BGR)

cv.namedWindow('Image',cv.WINDOW_AUTOSIZE)
cv.imshow('image',img)
cv.waitKey(0)

cv.imshow('image',hsv)
cv.waitKey(0)

cv.imshow('image',img_new)
cv.waitKey(0)
cv.destroyAllWindows()

plt.figure()
plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title("Original image")
plt.show()
plt.figure()
plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(hsv, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title("Saturation enhanced image")
plt.show()
plt.figure()
plt.imshow(cv.cvtColor(img_new, cv.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
plt.title("New image")
plt.show()
